1
00:00:32,664 --> 00:00:34,164
I don't care if this is the worst.

2
00:00:35,264 --> 00:00:36,574
If it means I can protect you.

3
00:00:38,874 --> 00:00:42,744
If I can make them feel my sorrow and rage,

4
00:00:44,144 --> 00:00:46,114
my very life and soul,

5
00:00:47,144 --> 00:00:48,414
I'd gladly give them up.

6
00:01:00,194 --> 00:01:02,664
How?

7
00:01:10,574 --> 00:01:13,604
What? No way, this is impossible.

8
00:01:22,244 --> 00:01:26,624
- A ghost! It's a ghost! - Sir!

9
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:29,894
What's going on out here?

10
00:01:42,564 --> 00:01:44,574
You are the lord of this chaos.

11
00:01:59,184 --> 00:02:00,184
No!

12
00:02:01,624 --> 00:02:02,784
No!

13
00:02:04,554 --> 00:02:05,654
What is this?

14
00:02:05,954 --> 00:02:07,764
How can a dead person be here?

15
00:02:08,424 --> 00:02:09,894
You're dead.

16
00:02:10,364 --> 00:02:13,404
- I know for a fact you're dead! - I was.

17
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:15,704
I did die.

18
00:02:17,634 --> 00:02:19,674
A dead woman came back from the grave.

19
00:02:24,744 --> 00:02:26,214
Just for you.

20
00:03:10,094 --> 00:03:13,564
(Pearl in Red)

21
00:03:16,494 --> 00:03:19,394
(Year 1997)

22
00:03:26,544 --> 00:03:27,974
(Episode 1)

23
00:03:32,544 --> 00:03:36,714
Don’t you worry. The fever’s broken, so everything will be all right.

24
00:03:37,754 --> 00:03:38,914
Oh, goodness, thank you.

25
00:03:39,954 --> 00:03:43,854
It really makes a difference having a nurse here.

26
00:03:47,294 --> 00:03:48,824
If it weren't for you,

27
00:03:49,664 --> 00:03:51,894
my grandson would've been in real trouble.

28
00:03:55,034 --> 00:03:57,204
I tried to handle it myself,

29
00:03:57,574 --> 00:03:59,304
but I just made the poor thing suffer more.

30
00:04:00,274 --> 00:04:04,674
Please don't say that. You're doing all you can for him.

31
00:04:06,044 --> 00:04:07,744
What good am I?

32
00:04:08,344 --> 00:04:11,414
Truth be told, he's the one who's keeping me going.

33
00:04:12,754 --> 00:04:15,724
After losing my son and his wife on the very same day,

34
00:04:16,124 --> 00:04:18,094
the only reason I'm still holding on...

35
00:04:18,554 --> 00:04:20,794
is all thanks to this little one.

36
00:04:21,494 --> 00:04:22,724
To me,

37
00:04:23,434 --> 00:04:27,864
he's my only family left, my only reason for living.

38
00:04:29,664 --> 00:04:32,734
I was so terrified I was going to lose my grandson too.

39
00:04:34,144 --> 00:04:36,844
I know that feeling all too well.

40
00:04:38,174 --> 00:04:42,684
I also have someone precious I'd do anything to protect.

41
00:04:43,084 --> 00:04:44,684
Of course you do.

42
00:04:45,554 --> 00:04:46,554
After all,

43
00:04:47,484 --> 00:04:49,954
you're a mother with your own child to protect now.

44
00:04:51,394 --> 00:04:52,924
Oh dear, anyway...

45
00:04:54,624 --> 00:04:59,664
I can't believe I made you come here when you're pregnant.

46
00:05:00,034 --> 00:05:04,734
You must've been tired all morning. I feel so bad for troubling you.

47
00:05:04,874 --> 00:05:05,934
I'm so sorry.

48
00:05:06,474 --> 00:05:10,474
- Not at all. I'm really okay. - How could you be?

49
00:05:11,614 --> 00:05:14,184
It must have been hard on the baby, too.

50
00:05:16,954 --> 00:05:18,184
Oh, little one.

51
00:05:18,784 --> 00:05:20,084
I'm sorry.

52
00:05:22,054 --> 00:05:24,254
See? My baby says it's okay.

53
00:05:26,794 --> 00:05:30,094
The baby's sweet because you are.

54
00:05:30,734 --> 00:05:32,394
Have you picked out a name yet?

55
00:05:33,764 --> 00:05:36,004
No, not yet.

56
00:05:36,264 --> 00:05:39,534
You should pick out a good name ahead of time.

57
00:05:40,074 --> 00:05:44,444
You don't want to rush to pick one for the birth certificate.

58
00:05:45,744 --> 00:05:46,784
I will.

59
00:05:55,154 --> 00:05:56,154
Honey.

60
00:05:58,894 --> 00:06:02,394
You're back early. Was your business trip cut short?

61
00:06:02,464 --> 00:06:05,834
Where have you been so early in the morning?

62
00:06:05,894 --> 00:06:08,634
I was at the blue-roofed house, down the hill.

63
00:06:09,034 --> 00:06:12,634
The woman who lives there is alone, so I helped with her sick grandson.

64
00:06:13,944 --> 00:06:16,844
You were nursing a sick child in your condition?

65
00:06:17,514 --> 00:06:19,044
All the way down the hill?

66
00:06:19,774 --> 00:06:21,014
It was really no trouble...

67
00:06:25,354 --> 00:06:28,454
It's not fine by my standards.

68
00:06:28,624 --> 00:06:30,724
Stop getting involved in things that don't concern you.

69
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:33,324
Stay away from the people down there.

70
00:06:33,524 --> 00:06:37,594
We are kept separate for a very good reason.

71
00:06:37,934 --> 00:06:41,364
You need to start acting like you belong up here, not down there.

72
00:06:52,714 --> 00:06:55,644
You must have rushed back from your trip...

73
00:06:55,914 --> 00:06:59,484
and been worried when I wasn't here this morning.

74
00:07:03,454 --> 00:07:07,524
I'm sorry for worrying you and for upsetting you.

75
00:07:19,334 --> 00:07:20,344
Here.

76
00:07:21,904 --> 00:07:24,044
- What's this? - Open it.

77
00:07:31,714 --> 00:07:33,324
It's a pearl necklace.

78
00:07:35,024 --> 00:07:37,054
That's right. Here.

79
00:07:39,354 --> 00:07:43,434
You know, these pearls...

80
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:47,334
They symbolize purity and nobility.

81
00:07:52,574 --> 00:07:56,874
A pure and noble gem born out of great suffering.

82
00:07:57,374 --> 00:08:01,384
Growing up without parents, enduring all sorts of indignities...

83
00:08:01,684 --> 00:08:02,784
That's you and me.

84
00:08:03,784 --> 00:08:05,954
It's the perfect jewel for us, don't you think?

85
00:08:06,214 --> 00:08:10,354
They say pearls help ensure a safe delivery, so take it.

86
00:08:10,894 --> 00:08:12,924
When I get back from my next business trip,

87
00:08:14,024 --> 00:08:16,294
I'll bring you even bigger pearls.

88
00:08:16,964 --> 00:08:17,964
Actually,

89
00:08:19,464 --> 00:08:23,404
- can I ask for something else? - What's that?

90
00:08:24,434 --> 00:08:28,744
Before we have the wedding, I'd like to register our marriage.

91
00:08:29,704 --> 00:08:34,144
Like you said, we can take our time with the wedding.

92
00:08:34,214 --> 00:08:37,284
In fact, I don't mind if we don't have a wedding at all.

93
00:08:37,884 --> 00:08:40,524
But with the baby coming soon,

94
00:08:41,584 --> 00:08:45,154
we need to be legally married to register the birth.

95
00:09:02,374 --> 00:09:04,414
Another business trip already? Without even a day of rest?

96
00:09:04,414 --> 00:09:06,344
Yes, I've got a lot to take care of.

97
00:09:08,614 --> 00:09:11,214
If this is about registering our marriage...

98
00:09:13,284 --> 00:09:15,084
I'll take care of it.

99
00:09:16,254 --> 00:09:18,194
Don't you worry about a thing.

100
00:09:18,924 --> 00:09:20,624
Just focus on yourself and the baby.

101
00:09:22,564 --> 00:09:25,634
Right. And about that money you asked for...

102
00:09:28,804 --> 00:09:32,234
The same amount as last time should be fine, right?

103
00:09:33,234 --> 00:09:35,474
Yes. I'm sorry to ask.

104
00:09:36,274 --> 00:09:37,774
This is already the third time.

105
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,044
You never even ask what it's for.

106
00:09:40,344 --> 00:09:41,644
That's...

107
00:09:42,784 --> 00:09:44,754
how much I trust you.

108
00:09:47,054 --> 00:09:49,084
And just as much as I trust you,

109
00:09:49,984 --> 00:09:52,054
I hope you can trust me too.

110
00:09:52,994 --> 00:09:56,424
I do trust you. More than you know.

111
00:10:00,134 --> 00:10:01,134
I'll get going.

112
00:10:07,504 --> 00:10:10,514
- Go inside. It's cold. - Have a safe trip.

113
00:10:32,094 --> 00:10:34,034
Maybe I shouldn't have said anything.

114
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:38,434
He's been so good to me, and he's just so lonely.

115
00:10:39,134 --> 00:10:40,844
I just made things awkward for him.

116
00:10:43,614 --> 00:10:47,284
I should apologise to your father when he gets back. Right?

117
00:10:50,044 --> 00:10:54,624
When you're born, we'll finally be a real family.

118
00:10:56,124 --> 00:10:59,524
Let's give your father the gift of a warm, loving family.

119
00:11:11,934 --> 00:11:16,474
Jung Ran, come on. Wait! Just wait a minute!

120
00:11:17,074 --> 00:11:19,074
Whatever you're thinking, this is not the answer.

121
00:11:19,144 --> 00:11:21,684
What are you talking about? Get out of my way!

122
00:11:21,744 --> 00:11:25,014
Come on, just use your head for a second.

123
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:29,284
She's pregnant and in the villa now, practically rubbing it in your face.

124
00:11:29,354 --> 00:11:33,254
I'm telling you, it's game over. Don't waste time getting worked up.

125
00:11:33,494 --> 00:11:36,994
Instead, maybe you and I can give it a go...

126
00:11:37,234 --> 00:11:38,564
Move your head already.

127
00:11:39,594 --> 00:11:41,334
How dare she try to steal him from me?

128
00:11:57,854 --> 00:11:58,854
You!

129
00:11:59,854 --> 00:12:02,184
You wretch!

130
00:12:03,024 --> 00:12:04,124
What is this?

131
00:12:04,494 --> 00:12:06,594
What gives you the right to barge into my home like this?

132
00:12:06,594 --> 00:12:09,264
Your home? I don't think so.

133
00:12:09,624 --> 00:12:12,334
Says the wretch who's shacked up in a home that isn't hers.

134
00:12:12,634 --> 00:12:15,664
How dare you throw yourself at my husband?

135
00:12:15,664 --> 00:12:16,834
Your husband?

136
00:12:16,974 --> 00:12:20,474
What? You think you've got it all because you're carrying his son?

137
00:12:20,774 --> 00:12:22,944
You saw him doting on his heir...

138
00:12:22,944 --> 00:12:24,274
and figured you were set, didn't you?

139
00:12:24,514 --> 00:12:27,444
You've got the villa, and now you're trying to replace me...

140
00:12:27,514 --> 00:12:28,644
as the lady of Adele Group?

141
00:12:29,344 --> 00:12:30,454
Wait a minute.

142
00:12:30,854 --> 00:12:33,924
Husband? I think you’re mistaken.

143
00:12:34,284 --> 00:12:37,454
- He told me he was a widower. - Right.

144
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:40,694
I'm standing here, kindly telling you...

145
00:12:40,694 --> 00:12:42,764
this isn't a mistake and I'm not dead.

146
00:12:43,664 --> 00:12:44,834
So listen up.

147
00:12:45,594 --> 00:12:47,834
Just because you gave him a son doesn't mean anything will change.

148
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:49,864
To Park Tae Ho,

149
00:12:50,474 --> 00:12:53,604
you're just a tool to give him an heir. That's all.

150
00:13:03,184 --> 00:13:06,814
Please, stop. If all this stress harms the baby,

151
00:13:06,884 --> 00:13:08,124
it's going to cause problems.

152
00:13:08,484 --> 00:13:11,654
Like I care! I've put up with enough.

153
00:13:11,894 --> 00:13:15,294
I let him cheat with a tramp since I couldn't give him a child.

154
00:13:15,564 --> 00:13:18,894
And I put up with being banished to the countryside for my health.

155
00:13:19,494 --> 00:13:21,634
But he brings this homewrecker into our villa?

156
00:13:22,604 --> 00:13:23,604
You said it yourself.

157
00:13:23,604 --> 00:13:25,704
Next, he'll move her into the master bedroom.

158
00:13:25,904 --> 00:13:28,174
Shouldn't I just nip it in the bud before that happens?

159
00:13:28,244 --> 00:13:31,714
I meant you should end things with your husband.

160
00:13:31,774 --> 00:13:32,774
Shut it!

161
00:13:35,614 --> 00:13:36,614
Darn.

162
00:13:37,384 --> 00:13:39,884
- What do you think you're doing? - What does it look like I'm doing?

163
00:13:40,554 --> 00:13:42,184
- Please, stop. - Let go of me.

164
00:13:43,424 --> 00:13:46,094
Stop it. Don't do it. Don't!

165
00:13:46,824 --> 00:13:47,864
You see that?

166
00:13:48,194 --> 00:13:50,264
Next time, it'll be your baby getting stomped on.

167
00:13:52,334 --> 00:13:54,804
If you want to protect your baby, then you'd better watch your step.

168
00:13:55,004 --> 00:13:58,004
Stay away from Park Tae Ho. Got it?

169
00:14:01,044 --> 00:14:02,044
Let's go.

170
00:14:23,294 --> 00:14:25,064
- President Park. - Right.

171
00:14:26,794 --> 00:14:28,934
- How's the baby? - The baby's fine.

172
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:33,874
So what are you going to do now?

173
00:14:35,404 --> 00:14:38,444
You lied about being married to get her to have your child,

174
00:14:38,674 --> 00:14:40,744
and now she knows you were just using her.

175
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:44,884
What if Nurse Kim just runs off? That would be a problem.

176
00:15:15,044 --> 00:15:16,044
I...

177
00:15:17,384 --> 00:15:18,884
More than anyone else's,

178
00:15:20,254 --> 00:15:22,024
I'll believe your words.

179
00:15:23,894 --> 00:15:24,954
So,

180
00:15:26,054 --> 00:15:29,224
whether it's an excuse or an explanation,

181
00:15:30,534 --> 00:15:32,094
just tell me the truth.

182
00:15:33,534 --> 00:15:36,964
Are you really a married man?

183
00:15:37,974 --> 00:15:39,674
You told me you were a widower.

184
00:15:40,474 --> 00:15:42,274
Was that a lie?

185
00:15:45,744 --> 00:15:47,814
It's true that my wife passed away.

186
00:15:48,544 --> 00:15:50,044
That marriage...

187
00:15:52,184 --> 00:15:53,584
That's how it ended.

188
00:15:55,984 --> 00:15:58,254
"That" marriage?

189
00:15:58,794 --> 00:16:00,694
Until five years ago,

190
00:16:00,994 --> 00:16:03,624
I was at Munhwadang, a well-known jewellery house,

191
00:16:04,564 --> 00:16:05,894
and I had married into the owner's family.

192
00:16:08,464 --> 00:16:10,574
My current business...

193
00:16:13,604 --> 00:16:14,974
is also in jewellery.

194
00:16:18,414 --> 00:16:20,414
(Adele, President Park Tae Ho)

195
00:16:20,474 --> 00:16:24,454
Five years ago, both my wife and father-in-law passed away,

196
00:16:26,754 --> 00:16:29,954
so I took over Munhwadang and made it the Adele you see today.

197
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:33,894
The woman who came to see you...

198
00:16:34,694 --> 00:16:37,794
is the one who helped me secure the inheritance from Munhwadang.

199
00:16:40,664 --> 00:16:43,704
It's just a marriage of convenience for the business.

200
00:16:45,674 --> 00:16:46,704
Even in the future,

201
00:16:48,074 --> 00:16:50,714
it'll be difficult to get a divorce.

202
00:16:55,784 --> 00:16:57,554
Don't look at me like that.

203
00:16:58,014 --> 00:17:01,924
Our child will legally be mine, and you'll continue...

204
00:17:03,854 --> 00:17:05,954
living a life in comfort.

205
00:17:07,324 --> 00:17:08,664
What are you talking about?

206
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:13,634
Is that really all you have to say to me?

207
00:17:15,304 --> 00:17:16,304
What else?

208
00:17:18,234 --> 00:17:20,274
Do you expect me to apologise or something?

209
00:17:23,004 --> 00:17:25,574
Just because you gave him a son doesn't mean anything will change.

210
00:17:26,144 --> 00:17:27,584
To Park Tae Ho,

211
00:17:28,244 --> 00:17:31,584
you're just a tool to give him an heir. That's all.

212
00:17:34,254 --> 00:17:35,254
Why...

213
00:17:36,154 --> 00:17:37,554
did you lie to me?

214
00:17:40,524 --> 00:17:42,724
Why didn't you say anything...

215
00:17:44,334 --> 00:17:46,264
until I was pregnant with your child?

216
00:17:50,334 --> 00:17:52,434
I did it for you.

217
00:17:54,344 --> 00:17:57,104
Have you already forgotten the circumstances of how we met?

218
00:18:00,144 --> 00:18:02,284
Do I owe you money or something?

219
00:18:02,544 --> 00:18:05,654
I already said no. Why won't you take no for an answer?

220
00:18:06,314 --> 00:18:09,824
I'm sorry. It's just that I'm really desperate.

221
00:18:10,054 --> 00:18:13,994
I don't care how desperate you are. You've only been here two weeks,

222
00:18:14,064 --> 00:18:16,224
and you're already hounding me for money?

223
00:18:17,024 --> 00:18:20,294
I gave you a chance because I heard you had it rough as an orphan.

224
00:18:20,734 --> 00:18:23,534
Do you have to act like you grew up without parents?

225
00:18:23,704 --> 00:18:24,704
Please...

226
00:18:25,334 --> 00:18:26,734
Please help me out just this once.

227
00:18:26,734 --> 00:18:30,144
That's an awful lot of money for a "one-time" favour.

228
00:18:30,344 --> 00:18:32,774
You're asking for an entire year's salary.

229
00:18:33,044 --> 00:18:35,244
Who's going to give you that kind of money?

230
00:18:36,784 --> 00:18:37,814
I will.

231
00:18:41,984 --> 00:18:45,324
That money may be hard for a family man to give up,

232
00:18:47,054 --> 00:18:50,564
but it's nothing for an orphan like me.

233
00:18:50,764 --> 00:18:51,764
Excuse me.

234
00:18:53,094 --> 00:18:54,964
Would you allow me to help you?

235
00:19:08,844 --> 00:19:10,884
I've wanted a child for a long time.

236
00:19:12,314 --> 00:19:14,854
My wife couldn't conceive.

237
00:19:16,624 --> 00:19:19,654
I was looking for another woman to bear my child.

238
00:19:19,654 --> 00:19:21,994
I came to see Dr. Do because of it,

239
00:19:22,294 --> 00:19:23,464
and that's when I saw you.

240
00:19:24,894 --> 00:19:25,894
So...

241
00:19:28,234 --> 00:19:31,474
From the very beginning, you were just planning on using me.

242
00:19:33,234 --> 00:19:34,444
From the very beginning...

243
00:19:34,904 --> 00:19:37,714
If I had told you everything from the start,

244
00:19:38,174 --> 00:19:40,714
if I'd said I was just paying you to have my child,

245
00:19:43,014 --> 00:19:44,714
you still would've taken my offer...

246
00:19:45,784 --> 00:19:46,814
and my money.

247
00:19:48,054 --> 00:19:49,754
You couldn't have turned it down.

248
00:19:51,324 --> 00:19:55,094
Because I kept my mouth shut, you got to play Cinderella,

249
00:19:56,064 --> 00:19:58,094
and live out a happy fantasy.

250
00:19:58,994 --> 00:20:01,004
- Am I wrong? - Stop!

251
00:20:01,004 --> 00:20:03,504
Stop being a fool and just look the other way.

252
00:20:03,964 --> 00:20:05,634
Keep pretending to be oblivious,

253
00:20:06,734 --> 00:20:07,744
and I'll let you stay...

254
00:20:09,104 --> 00:20:11,344
in this happy dream.

255
00:20:14,784 --> 00:20:18,154
My dream has already turned into a nightmare.

256
00:20:20,154 --> 00:20:22,284
The happiness I felt with you...

257
00:20:23,824 --> 00:20:25,624
was all just an illusion.

258
00:20:28,724 --> 00:20:30,364
The minute I get out of this hospital,

259
00:20:32,434 --> 00:20:33,594
I'm leaving you.

260
00:20:40,274 --> 00:20:43,804
You make leaving sound so easy.

261
00:20:47,544 --> 00:20:50,184
Did our relationship mean so little to you?

262
00:20:50,184 --> 00:20:53,284
You're the one who took our relationship so lightly.

263
00:20:53,354 --> 00:20:57,694
Fine, whatever you say. It doesn't change anything.

264
00:20:59,894 --> 00:21:02,294
Regardless of who started this casually,

265
00:21:03,494 --> 00:21:07,094
I have no intention of letting it end so easily. Got it?

266
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:13,634
It'd be a waste to lose a woman as perfect for the role as you.

267
00:21:14,274 --> 00:21:15,504
You're healthy, unmarried,

268
00:21:15,504 --> 00:21:17,344
and you have no family ties to complicate things.

269
00:21:17,344 --> 00:21:21,314
Plus, you're desperate for money, so I'll use you to the fullest.

270
00:21:22,084 --> 00:21:23,484
Right?

271
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:26,314
Isn't that right?

272
00:21:34,394 --> 00:21:35,894
Here.

273
00:21:37,894 --> 00:21:39,094
Here's that money you love so much.

274
00:21:39,364 --> 00:21:42,064
So take the money, shut your mouth, look the other way,

275
00:21:43,834 --> 00:21:45,404
and go on living in your nightmare.

276
00:21:48,944 --> 00:21:49,974
Oh, right.

277
00:21:49,974 --> 00:21:52,014
Considering all the money I've already given you,

278
00:21:53,114 --> 00:21:56,584
this isn't such a bad deal for you, is it?

279
00:22:41,164 --> 00:22:42,394
Hey, it's me.

280
00:22:45,694 --> 00:22:48,264
Could you send one of your guys over?

281
00:22:50,904 --> 00:22:54,004
Someone discreet who can run an errand for me.

282
00:22:56,604 --> 00:22:57,614
Right.

283
00:23:47,054 --> 00:23:49,764
If I had told you everything from the start,

284
00:23:50,664 --> 00:23:52,964
if I'd said I was just paying you to have my child,

285
00:23:54,504 --> 00:23:56,104
you still would've taken my offer...

286
00:23:57,034 --> 00:23:58,234
and my money.

287
00:23:59,474 --> 00:24:00,904
You couldn't have turned it down.

288
00:25:36,764 --> 00:25:37,774
This is driving me crazy.

289
00:25:42,344 --> 00:25:43,374
Jung Ran, come on.

290
00:25:43,374 --> 00:25:46,014
Let's just go back to the countryside.

291
00:25:46,214 --> 00:25:50,484
President Park must be furious. We need to lie low for a while.

292
00:25:52,214 --> 00:25:54,284
Lie low? Why should I?

293
00:25:54,754 --> 00:25:58,124
- I have nothing left to lose now. - Nothing to lose? That's absurd.

294
00:25:58,594 --> 00:26:01,194
The only reason you're not going in is because you're scared of him too.

295
00:26:01,464 --> 00:26:03,694
You're just sitting here, chewing apples you don't even like.

296
00:26:03,764 --> 00:26:05,894
I know you're just stalling.

297
00:26:06,464 --> 00:26:08,104
As if you know anything.

298
00:26:09,264 --> 00:26:13,474
I'm not eating these to stall. I'm eating to get my strength up.

299
00:26:13,734 --> 00:26:17,344
I'm stocking up on strength before I face Park Tae Ho.

300
00:26:30,424 --> 00:26:31,424
What's with you?

301
00:26:31,754 --> 00:26:33,854
If you're going in there to say your piece,

302
00:26:34,694 --> 00:26:36,864
I can't just stand by. Not as a man.

303
00:26:37,564 --> 00:26:38,764
A man? Please.

304
00:26:40,434 --> 00:26:42,734
Fine. If that's how it is, then come in with me and...

305
00:26:43,834 --> 00:26:45,434
I'll go get you some more apples.

306
00:26:46,304 --> 00:26:47,304
Apples?

307
00:26:48,544 --> 00:26:50,744
You'll need more if you run out of juice mid-argument.

308
00:26:52,644 --> 00:26:56,014
You can count on me. I'll man up...

309
00:26:56,184 --> 00:26:59,054
and get you the reddest, tartest ones I can find.

310
00:27:00,254 --> 00:27:01,254
All right?

311
00:27:06,754 --> 00:27:08,994
Figures. That darn coward.

312
00:27:09,164 --> 00:27:12,464
I should've let him freeze to death. I regret ever helping him.

313
00:27:13,194 --> 00:27:15,334
I've put up with him for ten years,

314
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:17,434
and he's still only good for driving.

315
00:27:22,104 --> 00:27:23,204
Whatever.

316
00:27:23,774 --> 00:27:25,974
I can handle Tae Ho just fine on my own.

317
00:27:26,944 --> 00:27:29,644
I didn't fight this hard to become the lady of Adele Group for nothing.

318
00:27:51,874 --> 00:27:53,974
Goodness, you scared me!

319
00:27:54,844 --> 00:27:56,244
You scared the wits out of me.

320
00:27:57,444 --> 00:28:01,114
How dare you set foot in my house after what you did?

321
00:28:02,284 --> 00:28:03,484
Get lost this second.

322
00:28:03,944 --> 00:28:06,514
This is my house too.

323
00:28:07,154 --> 00:28:09,254
After all I went through to become the lady of Adele Group?

324
00:28:10,584 --> 00:28:11,594
What the...

325
00:28:12,224 --> 00:28:15,164
I'd give you up before I'd give up my place in this house.

326
00:28:17,094 --> 00:28:18,194
Oh Jung Ran.

327
00:28:19,294 --> 00:28:21,764
My patience with you has run out.

328
00:28:22,634 --> 00:28:25,774
Go back to the countryside and don't make a peep.

329
00:28:26,134 --> 00:28:28,944
I can't. Over my dead body.

330
00:28:30,774 --> 00:28:32,374
I have a stake in this family too.

331
00:28:33,174 --> 00:28:34,344
You may think you're high and mighty,

332
00:28:34,344 --> 00:28:35,744
but none of this would be yours...

333
00:28:35,744 --> 00:28:37,114
if I hadn't tampered with your late father-in-law's will.

334
00:28:37,744 --> 00:28:40,514
You only got his entire fortune thanks to me.

335
00:28:41,214 --> 00:28:44,754
Ever since, I've done everything you asked and put up with it all.

336
00:28:45,494 --> 00:28:49,294
You could at least cut me some slack this one time.

337
00:28:49,894 --> 00:28:51,994
How much more slack do I have to give you?

338
00:28:53,164 --> 00:28:55,404
You were my late wife's maid, but I took you in...

339
00:28:55,404 --> 00:28:57,664
and made you the lady of this house.

340
00:28:57,834 --> 00:28:59,734
I put up with you for five years...

341
00:28:59,734 --> 00:29:01,644
even though you couldn't give me a son.

342
00:29:02,044 --> 00:29:04,844
I have shown you more patience than you could ever deserve.

343
00:29:05,544 --> 00:29:09,584
And you still have the audacity to go after my son?

344
00:29:11,314 --> 00:29:13,354
If I hadn't been so patient, you...

345
00:29:16,184 --> 00:29:18,254
You would already be in your coffin.

346
00:29:20,794 --> 00:29:21,794
Darling...

347
00:29:21,894 --> 00:29:24,464
If you understand me, get out now!

348
00:29:37,804 --> 00:29:38,814
What's this?

349
00:29:46,014 --> 00:29:47,254
Explain yourself. Now.

350
00:30:03,604 --> 00:30:06,334
(Dongwoo University Hospital)

351
00:30:08,074 --> 00:30:09,074
Dan Hui!

352
00:30:11,874 --> 00:30:13,144
Dan Hui, no!

353
00:30:32,894 --> 00:30:33,894
Dan Hui.

354
00:30:35,434 --> 00:30:36,464
Please, don't do this.

355
00:30:39,434 --> 00:30:41,004
Come to me, please.

356
00:30:44,644 --> 00:30:45,744
Please.

357
00:30:57,724 --> 00:30:58,754
Dan Hui!

358
00:31:23,584 --> 00:31:26,514
(Pearl in Red)

359
00:31:26,984 --> 00:31:28,184
She's refusing the surgery?

360
00:31:28,254 --> 00:31:31,354
It's a real shame. Her younger sister has cancer,

361
00:31:31,454 --> 00:31:33,524
but she's stubbornly refusing the surgery.

362
00:31:33,594 --> 00:31:36,794
I'm begging you, Dan Hui. Please, live for me.

363
00:31:36,864 --> 00:31:39,494
- What's with that look? - It's none of your business.

364
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:42,664
I'm pregnant with the child you've always wanted.

365
00:31:42,834 --> 00:31:46,674
- I guess I'll have to end it. - You can't mean...

366
00:31:46,734 --> 00:31:47,734
You know this person, right?

367
00:31:47,734 --> 00:31:49,704
I'm on the job and could use your help.

368
00:31:50,244 --> 00:31:52,474
Hold on. The patient, Kim Dan Hui, is missing.

369
00:31:52,574 --> 00:31:56,244
Dan Hui? Dan Hui! Over here. Is anybody there?

370
00:31:56,384 --> 00:31:58,584
Somebody help! Over here!
